responses.text:
O God, thou art my guiding star;
That shines so bright from near and far;
When night's dark veil doth lift and fade,
Thy love remains, my heart's sweet shade.

O God! Thou art my sheltering wing;
That keeps me safe from life's fierce sting;
When sorrow's waves crash on the shore,
Thy comfort stays, forever more.

O God, thou art my morning dew;
That gently falls, my soul anew;
In thy refreshing, cooling rain,
I find my heart, my life, my gain.
